      "content": "While visible trends can certainly suggest a correlation, attributing the entire participation decline solely to safety net generosity oversimplifies a highly dynamic labor market. Policy researchers caution that viewing it as a simple \"trade-off\" ignores how programs are often designed to support workforce transitions. Therefore, while disincentives are a documented concern, the data likely reflects a combination of safety net structures interacting with broader macroeconomic pressures.",
